<item>
            <title>[FLINK-32029] FutureUtils.handleUncaughtException swallows exceptions that are caused by the exception handler code</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-32029</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I ran into an issue in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-31773&quot; title=&quot;Separate DefaultLeaderElectionService.start(LeaderContender) into two separate methods for starting the driver and registering a contender&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-31773&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-31773&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; where the passed exception handler relies on the &lt;tt&gt;leaderContender&lt;/tt&gt; field of the &lt;tt&gt;DefaultLeaderElectionService&lt;/tt&gt;. This field can become &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt; with the changes of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-31773&quot; title=&quot;Separate DefaultLeaderElectionService.start(LeaderContender) into two separate methods for starting the driver and registering a contender&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-31773&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-31773&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. But the &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt; check was missed in the error handling code. This bug wasn&apos;t exposed because &lt;tt&gt;FutureUtils.handleUncaughtException(..)&lt;/tt&gt; expects the passed error handler callback to be bug-free.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
